overview: The user wanted to significantly improve the visual appeal of their
  sleep questionnaire app. I began by conducting a detailed code review to
  understand the existing styling, identifying areas like the generic color
  palette, plain backgrounds, and basic form elements as needing improvement.
  The approach involved implementing a new, calming sleep-themed color palette,
  redesigning the main form layout with subtle decorative elements, and
  enhancing core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and
  progress bars. All 14 questionnaire sections, including the intro and report,
  were updated to ensure consistent application of the new theme, replacing old
  gray boxes with refined card-style groupings and themed headers. During this
  process, a React console error related to  values being passed to input
  components was identified and fixed by safely converting  to an empty
  string in the  component. The outcome is a much more polished,
  cohesive, and thematically appropriate application, with improved visual
  hierarchy and user feedback.
